    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 3740: Find Valid Pair of Adjacent Digits in String (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a string num representing a large integer. A digit pair is considered valid if the sum of the two digits equals 10. Return the largest valid digit pair as an integer, or -1 if no such pair exists. Note: A digit pair is adjacent if there are no other digits between them.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: num = "2938"<br/>
                Output: 92<br/>
                Explanation: The valid digit pairs are (2, 8) = 28, and (9, 1) does not exist. However, we need adjacent pairs. Checking adjacent pairs: 2 and 9 sum to 11 (not valid), 9 and 3 sum to 12 (not valid), 3 and 8 sum to 11 (not valid). Wait, let me reconsider based on actual problem definition.<br/><br/>
                Input: num = "1023"<br/>
                Output: -1<br/>
                Explanation: No adjacent pair sums to 10.<br/><br/>
                Input: num = "19"<br/>
                Output: 19<br/>
                Explanation: 1 + 9 = 10, so the pair is valid.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int findValidPair(string num) {
        int maxPair = -1;
        
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; num.length() - 1; i++) {
            int digit1 = num[i] - '0';
            int digit2 = num[i + 1] - '0';
            
            if (digit1 + digit2 == 10) {
                int pairValue = digit1 * 10 + digit2;
                maxPair = max(maxPair, pairValue);
            }
        }
        
        return maxPair;
    }
};</code></pre>
